<paragraph id="8BB6368C92547737FF43F825FAADBC97" blockId="4.[136,1452,1929,2066]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1452,158,617]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92547736FF43F825FE2AB444" bold="true" box="[189,443,2037,2063]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92547736FE45F825FD42B444" box="[443,723,2037,2063]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92547736FE26F825FD42B444" box="[472,723,2037,2063]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">Bertolonia alternifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992547736FC6AF826FB91B459" box="[916,1024,2038,2066]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.193" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="km" value="4.193">4.193 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992547736FB57F826FA89B459" box="[1193,1304,2038,2066]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.402" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="km" value="1.402">1.402 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92557737FCF2FF4EFC33BCF3" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[780,930,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found in the “Serra do Peito de Moça” inside the “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras” and in areas bordering the park.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92557737FF43FF36FA81BE23" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FF43FF36FE98BD4B" bold="true" box="[189,265,230,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FED8FF36FDB4BD4B" box="[294,549,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FED8FF36FDB4BD4B" box="[294,549,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92557737FD2BFF36FC88BD4B" box="[725,793,230,256]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests and cloud forests (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992557737FA80FF36FF34BD6F" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers from September to April and fruits from September to May. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FB71FEDAFA1EBD6F" box="[1167,1423,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FB71FEDAFA1EBD6F" box="[1167,1423,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium, and sepals densely glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FA7FFEFEFF25BD26" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
long), alternate leaves, blades 3.4–7.3 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FD7CFE82FC92BD26" box="[642,771,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="2.2">2.2–5.8 cm</quantity>
, flowers with long petals (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FBD3FE82FB36BD26" box="[1069,1191,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="11.0">11–18 mm</quantity>
) and long anthers (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FA7EFE82FF24BDDA" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
) with extrorse pores. Along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FDD5FEA6FCD3BDDB" box="[555,834,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FDD5FEA6FCD3BDDB" box="[555,834,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FCAEFEA7FC7CBDDB" box="[848,1005,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FCAEFEA7FC7BBDDB" box="[848,1002,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">B. kollmannii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FBDDFEA7FA3ABDDB" box="[1059,1451,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FBDDFEA7FB35BDDB" box="[1059,1188,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violacea">B. violacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FB51FEA6FA3ABDDB" box="[1199,1451,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">Bertolonia alternifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has the smallest leaves in the genus (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FDD7FE4AFD39BDFE" box="[553,680,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="4.9" valueMax="7.3" valueMin="2.5">2.5–7.3 cm</quantity>
long). A recently published species from the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92557737FAFAFE4AFA39BDFF" box="[1284,1448,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FF76FE6EFD43BD93" authority="Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg" authorityName="Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg" box="[136,722,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michelangeliana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FF76FE6EFE53BD93" box="[136,450,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia michelangeliana</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92557737FD01FE6EFB97BD92" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[767,1030,446,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" pagination="1663 - 1676" refId="ref18480" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2017) Flora do Espirito Santo: Bertolonia (Melastomataceae). Rodriguesia 68 (5): 1663 - 1676. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201768510" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FCB8FE6FFCE9BD93" box="[838,888,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. 2017: 1670
</bibRefCitation>
) also has alternate leaves and anthers with extrorse pores. They differ by the shorter petioles (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FD06FE32FCE7BDB6" box="[760,886,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–5.5 cm</quantity>
long) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FC22FE33FBE8BDB7" box="[988,1145,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FC22FE33FBE8BDB7" box="[988,1145,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">B. alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FB74FE33FB30BDB7" box="[1162,1185,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">vs</emphasis>
. longer, 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FAFDFE32FA1FBDB6" box="[1283,1422,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" metricValueMax="13.6" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="8.4" valueMax="13.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2–13.6 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92557737FF76FDD7FEF3BE6B" box="[136,354,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michelangeliana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FF76FDD7FEF3BE6B" box="[136,354,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">B. michelangeliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leaves with 3–5 main veins (v 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FD3AFDD7FD5EBE6B" box="[708,719,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">s</emphasis>
. 7–9 main veins), flowers with only glandulose-punctate pedicels and bigger petals, with 11–18 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FE13FDFAFDFDBE0E" box="[493,620,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="7.0">7–10.5 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FD85FDFBFD03BE0F" box="[635,658,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">vs</emphasis>
. flowers with glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose pedicels and smaller petals, with 10–13 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992557737FE03FD9EFDE2BE22" box="[509,627,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="6.6" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="6.0">6–7.2 mm</quantity>
). For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92557737FC88FD9FFB11BE23" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B." box="[886,1152,590,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" pagination="273 - 279" refId="ref18825" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B. (2011) Two new species of Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Kew Bulletin 66: 273 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 011 - 9281 - 0" type="journal article" year="2011">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92557737FC06FD9FFBB8BE23" box="[1016,1065,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792557737FB48FD9EFA9BBE23" box="[1206,1290,590,616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
